bspline-fortran
------------------------------------------
The library provides subroutines for 1D-6D interpolation and extrapolation
using B-splines. The code is written in modern Fortran (i.e., Fortran 2003+).
There are two ways to use the module, via a basic subroutine interface and an
object-oriented interface. Both are thread safe.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.2.0-1
  libbspline-fortran-devel-6.1.0-1bl1
  libbspline-fortran6-6.1.0-1bl1
  libgfortran5-11.2.0-1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.37-2
  cmake-3.20.0-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  gcc-fortran-11.2.0-1
  ninja-1.10.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/jacobwilliams/bspline-fortran

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/jacobwilliams/bspline-fortran.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bspline-fortran-6.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bspline-fortran-6.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bspline-fortran-6.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bspline-fortran-6.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbspline-fortran6-6.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbspline-fortran-devel-6.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(bspline-fortran)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/bspline-fortran.README
  /usr/share/doc/bspline-fortran/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/bspline-fortran/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/bspline-fortran/bspline-fortran.md

(libbspline-fortran6)
  /usr/bin/cygbspline-fortran-6.dll

(libbspline-fortran-devel)
  /usr/include/bspline_kinds_module.mod
  /usr/include/bspline_module.mod
  /usr/include/bspline_oo_module.mod
  /usr/include/bspline_sub_module.mod
  /usr/lib/libbspline-fortran.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/bspline-fortran.pc

